From 5255af549d4df55dc3439f2fafc2163332168824 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcos <marcosbrendonaz@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 17:30:57 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] feat: complete anti-fingerprinting system with 14 modules

Chameleon Browser anti-fingerprinting system implemented natively in C++.
Defeats Fingerprint Pro with unique visitor IDs per profile.

Modules (Blink layer):
- Canvas noise (getImageData, toDataURL, toBlob, measureText)
- WebGL noise (readPixels, renderer/vendor spoofing, params, extensions shuffle)
- Audio noise (getChannelData, OfflineAudioContext.startRendering)
- WebRTC IP leak protection (filter host/srflx/prflx candidates)
- DeviceMemory spoofing (consistent with hardware profile)
- ClientRects sub-pixel noise
- Screen spoofing (colorDepth, availHeight, outerHeight)
- Locale override (navigator.language, Intl.DateTimeFormat locale)
- Font enumeration blocking (OS-aware, measureText noise)
- Navigator spoofing (platform, userAgent, hardwareConcurrency, maxTouchPoints)
- Hardware identity profiles (24 realistic OS+GPU+cores+RAM combinations)
- Brand spoofing via --chameleon-brand flag (configurable without rebuild)
- Timezone spoofing (consistent with locale, via CHAMELEON_TZ env var)

Modules (V8 layer):
- Math noise (tan, sin, cos, atan2, log, exp, sinh, cosh, tanh)

Infrastructure:
- ChameleonNoise utility class with FNV-1a deterministic noise
- Modular system via --chameleon-modules flag
- Switch propagation to renderer processes
- CHAMELEON_SEED/CHAMELEON_TZ env vars for V8/ICU integration
- Night build cron system (night_build.cjs)
- Leak check diagnostic script (leak_check.js)

