+# CLAUDE.md
+
+This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.
+
+## Project Overview
+
+Chameleon Browser is a Chromium fork with native C++ anti-fingerprinting protections. The branch `chameleon/dev` contains all Chameleon modifications on top of upstream Chromium. The goal is to make each browser profile produce a unique, deterministic fingerprint that resists cross-profile tracking by services like Fingerprint Pro.
+
+There is a **reference implementation** at `C:\Users\Marcos\Desktop\TEeste\packages\chameleon\src\noise\` — a JS injection-based version (using Patchright/Playwright) that successfully defeats Fingerprint Pro. Our Chromium C++ implementation must match its behavior. Always compare against the reference when adding or debugging modules.
+
+## Build Commands
+
+```bash
+# Incremental build (only recompiles changed files) - default 16 threads
+build_chameleon.bat
+
+# Full rebuild (runs gn gen first) - required after changing .gn/.gni files or args.gn
+build_chameleon.bat --full
+
+# From MSYS2/bash shell (Claude Code context)
+export DEPOT_TOOLS_WIN_TOOLCHAIN=0
+/c/depot_tools/autoninja -C out/Default chrome -j 16
+```
+
+Build config is at `out/Default/args.gn`. Current config: release build with `is_debug=false`, `is_component_build=true`, `symbol_level=0`.
+
+When only `.cc`/`.h` files change, incremental build works automatically. When `.gn`/`.gni` files or `args.gn` change, use `--full` or run `gn gen out/Default` manually.
+
+## Running / Testing
+
+```bash
+# Interactive launcher with profile management and module selection
+run_chameleon.bat
+
+# Direct CLI launch (all modules)
+out\Default\chrome.exe --user-data-dir="E:\chameleon_profiles\<name>" --chameleon-seed=<hex> --chameleon-locale=en-US,en --js-flags="--chameleon-math-noise --chameleon-math-seed=0x<hex>"
+
+# Specific modules only
+out\Default\chrome.exe --user-data-dir="..." --chameleon-seed=<hex> --chameleon-modules=canvas,webgl,audio,navigator,fonts
+
+# All modules disabled (baseline test)
+out\Default\chrome.exe --user-data-dir="..." --chameleon-seed=<hex> --chameleon-modules=none
+```
+
+Profiles stored at `E:\chameleon_profiles\`. Each profile has a unique `chameleon_seed.txt` (128-bit hex, crypto-generated). Same seed = same fingerprint.
+
+Test sites: fingerprint.com (primary target), browserleaks.com/canvas, browserleaks.com/webgl, browserleaks.com/webrtc, audiofingerprint.openwpm.com
+
+## Night Build System
+
+`night_build.cjs` is a cron-like Bun script that monitors the clock and runs builds between 3 AM - 7 AM. Run with `bun night_build.cjs`. It checks every 20 seconds and calls `gn gen` + `autoninja -j 16`.
+
+## Architecture: Chameleon Anti-Fingerprinting System
+
+### Core Infrastructure
+
+- **`third_party/blink/renderer/core/chameleon/chameleon_noise.h/.cc`** — Central utility class. Reads `--chameleon-seed` from CommandLine, provides deterministic noise via FNV-1a hash. `IsModuleEnabled(subsystem_id)` checks a bitmask populated from `--chameleon-modules`. All Blink-layer protection modules call into this class.
+- **`third_party/blink/public/common/switches.h` / `third_party/blink/common/switches.cc`** — Declares `kChameleonSeed`, `kChameleonLocale`, `kChameleonModules` command-line switches.
+- **`third_party/blink/renderer/core/chameleon/build.gni`** — GN include that adds Chameleon source files to the Blink core build. Imported by `third_party/blink/renderer/core/BUILD.gn`.
+
+### Anti-Fingerprint Modules (Blink layer)
+
+Each module guards its changes with `ChameleonNoise::IsModuleEnabled(kSubsystem...)`:
+
+| Module | ID | Flag | Files Modified | What it does |
+|--------|---:|------|----------------|--------------|
+| Canvas | 1 | `canvas` | `base_rendering_context_2d.cc`, `html_canvas_element.cc` | Pixel noise on getImageData/toDataURL/toBlob, measureText width noise |
+| WebGL | 2,11 | `webgl` | `webgl_rendering_context_base.cc` | readPixels noise, invisible tag on RENDERER/VENDOR strings |
+| WebGL Params | 13 | `webglparams` | `webgl_rendering_context_base.cc` | Spoofs MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE etc, shuffles getSupportedExtensions |
+| Audio | 3 | `audio` | `audio_buffer.cc`, `offline_audio_context.cc` | Noise on getChannelData (every 50 samples) + OfflineAudioContext.startRendering |
+| WebRTC | 4 | `webrtc` | `rtc_peer_connection.cc` | Filters host/srflx/prflx ICE candidates (C++ level) |
+| DeviceMemory | 5 | `memory` | `navigator_device_memory.cc` | Returns seed-derived value from {2, 4, 8, 16} |
+| ClientRects | 6 | `rects` | `element.cc` | Sub-pixel noise on getBoundingClientRect/getClientRects |
+| Screen | 7 | `screen` | `screen.cc`, `local_dom_window.cc` | colorDepth=32, pixelDepth=32, seed-derived taskbar offset on availHeight + outerHeight |
+| Locale | 8 | `locale` | `navigator_language.cc` | Overrides navigator.language/languages via --chameleon-locale |
+| Fonts | 9 | `fonts` | `font_cache.cc`, `base_rendering_context_2d.cc`, `text_metrics.h` | Blocks ~30% non-safe fonts, adds measureText width noise |
+| Navigator | 12 | `navigator` | `navigator_concurrent_hardware.cc`, `navigator.cc`, `navigator_events.cc` | Spoofs hardwareConcurrency, platform, maxTouchPoints |
+
+### Math Noise Module (V8 layer)
+
+Math noise operates inside V8, not Blink. It uses V8 flags instead of `ChameleonNoise`:
+
+- **`v8/src/flags/flag-definitions.h`** — Defines `--chameleon-math-noise` (bool) and `--chameleon-math-seed` (uint64).
+- **`v8/src/builtins/builtins-math.cc`** — C++ BUILTINs: `ChameleonMathTan`, `ChameleonMathSin`, `ChameleonMathCos`, `ChameleonMathAtan2`, `ChameleonMathLog`, `ChameleonMathExp`, `ChameleonMathSinh`, `ChameleonMathCosh`, `ChameleonMathTanh`. Uses multiplicative noise `r * (1 + noise)` at ~1e-14 level (matching reference). Skips result==0 and !isFinite.
+- **`v8/src/builtins/builtins-definitions.h`** — Registers all 9 Chameleon math builtins as CPP builtins.
+- **`v8/src/init/bootstrapper.cc`** — Conditionally installs Chameleon builtins when `v8_flags.chameleon_math_noise` is true, replacing the Torque-generated originals. The JIT (js-call-reducer.cc) won't inline CPP builtins, so noise is preserved even in optimized code.
+- Activated via `--js-flags="--chameleon-math-noise --chameleon-math-seed=0x<seed>"` (handled by `run_chameleon.bat`).
+- **V8 builtin pattern**: Use `args.atOrUndefined(isolate, N)` to get arguments, then `Object::ToNumber` with a local `Handle<Object>` variable. Never use `ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION` with `args.at()` directly (it's a temporary).
+
+### Font Protection (Platform layer)
+
+Font enumeration blocking lives in `platform/fonts/font_cache.cc` which cannot import from `core/`. It reads `--chameleon-seed` and `--chameleon-modules` directly from `base::CommandLine` with its own seed parser and FNV-1a hash. Blocks ~30% of non-safe fonts based on seed hash. Safe fonts (Arial, Verdana, Segoe UI, etc.) are never blocked. Additionally, `measureText` in `base_rendering_context_2d.cc` applies multiplicative width noise via `TextMetrics::SetWidth()`.
+
+### Pattern for Adding New Modules
+
+1. Add a new `kSubsystem*` constant in `chameleon_noise.h`
+2. Add the module name mapping in `ModuleNameToBit()` in `chameleon_noise.cc`
+3. In the target Blink file, add `#include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/chameleon/chameleon_noise.h"`
+4. Guard changes with `if (ChameleonNoise::IsModuleEnabled(ChameleonNoise::kSubsystem*)) { ... }`
+5. If the file is in `platform/` (not `core/`), use `base::CommandLine` directly instead of `ChameleonNoise`
+6. If the file is in `v8/`, use V8 flags (`v8_flags.*`) and register in `builtins-definitions.h` + `bootstrapper.cc`
+7. Update `run_chameleon.bat` module list and help text
+8. Compare behavior against the reference implementation in `C:\Users\Marcos\Desktop\TEeste\packages\chameleon\src\noise\`
+
+## Key Constraints
+
+- **platform/ cannot depend on core/**: The Blink `platform/` layer has no access to `ChameleonNoise`. Use `base::CommandLine` directly (see `font_cache.cc` for the pattern).
+- **V8 has no access to Blink**: V8 modules use V8 flags (`v8_flags.*`) instead of Blink's `ChameleonNoise`. Pass seed via `--js-flags`.
+- **Debug vs Release**: Debug builds (`is_debug=true`) enable DCHECKs that cause STATUS_BREAKPOINT crashes on complex pages (e.g., fingerprint.com CSS animations in style_resolver.cc). Always use release build (`is_debug=false`, `dcheck_always_on=false`) for testing.
+- **`is_component_build=true`**: Builds many small DLLs for faster incremental linking. Keep this on for development.
+- **Chromium is huge**: ~28k+ build targets. Full rebuild takes 5+ hours. Always prefer incremental builds.
+- **Noise must be deterministic**: Same seed must produce same fingerprint across sessions. Use FNV-1a hash with seed, never `rand()`.
+- **Noise must be multiplicative for Math**: The reference uses `r * (1 + noise)` not `r + noise`. Additive noise doesn't affect fingerprinting services that check ratios.
+
+## Not Yet Implemented (compared to reference)
+
+- `Date.prototype.getTimezoneOffset` spoofing (requires V8 changes)
+- `Intl.DateTimeFormat` timezone spoofing (requires V8 changes)
+- These are lower priority since timezone is already exposed by the user's IP/proxy.
